data.title: David Fisher Service Details - Martinsburg, West Virginia
data.meta_description: David Frank Fisher, 67, of Martinsburg,  passed away on Saturday, September 8, 2018 at his home.  Born April 13, 1951, in Washington D.C. he was the son of the late Russell and Marie Fisher.  He was a Veteran of the United States Navy and a member of the Moose and the American Legion. David was a retired engineer for Airpax in Frederick Maryland.  He is survived by his wife Linda Susan Davenport Fisher; Son David wife Angi of Frederick; Son Dustin partner Holly of Martinsburg; Son Adam partner Brooke of Martinsburg; Daughter Amy husband Justin of Martinsburg. Also brother Russell Fisher of Myersville; and sisters Nancy Fisher of Fairfield; Lynn Fisher of Frederick; Rose Wivell of Emmitsburg; Anna Fisher of Frederick; and Annabelle Toms of Thurmont. He was PawPaw to grandchildren Abigail, Addison, Caitlyn and Alex.   David loved playing golf, NASCAR, the Redskins, and going to the Outer Banks with his fishing buddies.  A remembrance service will be held for family and friends at a later date.
